We were just walking by, and were immediately enticed by the fun salsa/latin beat, savory aroma and fantastic vibes pouring out of this establishment. When we saw their happy hour selections, we were sold (5-7pm!). Outstanding Piña-Coladas, Mohitos, and Margaritas confirmed our anticipation, delicious and only six bucks. $3 draught beers, more fantastic music and THE BEST fried yucca were also enjoyed. This place is so fun, affordable and the kitchen is one of the most professional in the area. Mario was the most welcoming of bar tenders, as he happily explained the menu, their story and some of the dance classes that are offered (prior to covid). We felt safe being served outside and will be back FOR SURE. Especially for some dance lessons! P.S. for the authentic cuban experience, finish your meal with a shot of aguardiente! Delicious!

Most underrated food spot and hidden in Adams Morgan. Every single dish I tried is amazing! I always start with the  fresh made Nachos. I also love their happy hours, which ends at 7pm. I go for the margaritas and they are tasty and strong. Great and courteous service!

We had the guacamole, empanadas and the Cuban sandwich. The sandwich was a real Cuban, like my mother’s. The music was perfect and we had a great time. The place was spotless, everybody wearing masks. I highly recommend this place.

I've been living in Adams Morgan for the past four years and this place has definitely become a regular spot for my friends and I. The food is delicious, the drinks are refreshing, and the staff is always friendly, attentive, and especially safe in the COVID-era. Plus, the ambiance of the place is perfect for a date, dinner with parents, or a quick drinks with friends. I definitely suggest this place to anyone looking for a bite to eat in Adams Morgan or NW DC.

After seeing this restaurant on a restaurant.com deal, we decided to give it a try. We are beyond impressed with the authenticity and taste of the food! We were lucky to visit during happy hour, and the drink selections on the list were amazing. The mojito was so refreshing and they even added strawberry to enhance the flavor. I ordered two! We ordered the nachos with chicken to start and it was fulfilling enough for two. We also order the Paella for one, which was still filling for two. Both dishes were delicious and graciously portioned. They have outside seating and staff is definitely a Covid-19 compliant. We are excited to visit again!

This cuban restaurant in the heart of Adams Morgan is a MUST for all DC residents and visitors!!! You will not be disappointed by the incredible food served in large portions and FULL of flavor! The cuban-music softly playing around you, the lights hanging above you, the fresh-made mojitos and the kindness and smiles from the staff will having you coming back again and again. They are taking safety precautions seriously - hand sanitizer, masked staff, and socially distant tables. They also have bug spray available for anyone who needs it while you sit a cozy and comfortable table outside! We cannot recommend this spot enough!!!!!!!

Habana Village is a spot you MUST try, sooner rather than later! New management of this incredible gem in Adams Morgan has brought a feeling of Cuba to DC. Fantastic & inviting staff, DELICIOUS food, and cuban music-filled ambiance with hanging lights above the outdoor seating make this the perfect spot on any evening. The menu is filled with options (the trio de empanadas appetizer is delicious!), all at great values for the amount of food you get, and each dish is just as incredible and flavorful as the next!! The drinks are fresh and made from scratch and you won't find a better mojito in the area (the whiskey mojito is our favorite!). As soon as you arrive you are greeted by the nicest staff, who will ensure your evening is comfortable and that you are well taken care of.  They take safety precautions seriously - you will find hand sanitizer, socially distant tables, and a fully masked staff at all times. We cannot recommend this restaurant to enough people!!!

I can’t believe I hadn’t found this restaurant sooner! Wonderful staff, great service, and delicious food. It’s the perfect place for affordable, yet delicious food served in Abuela approved portions. They also have plenty of drink selections from the bar. The aesthetic and ambiance take you back to old school, classic Cuban restaurants, especially with the great dance music (which you can dance to while you’re there.) Habana Village will now be a regular stop for me and my family and friends whenever I’m traveling through DC.

I would give this place 5 stars if it wasn't that the DJ keeps undermining everything. At the beginning (9pm or so) when hardly anybody is there  he plays very good salsa, usually Colombian salsa (he is Colombian). Then as people start to arrive he plays the obligatory tacky bachatas and useless merengues which is OK, but when it's the turn for salsa he goes away from the traditional and starts playing some strange almost psychedelic salsa, sometimes influenced by reggeaton which keeps the true salsa dancers from getting the right "feeling" for a good dance. This nonsense continues the whole night and gets worse as then he plays salsa influenced by Cuban timba which again confuses the true salsa dancers. It's almost as if he is trying to show everybody there that he knows about all the different genres of Latin music. In particular he feels obligated to play bachatas (wish they would disappear) but seldom plays cha-cha-cha's. They're not in his radar. What  kind of Latin DJ is this? Unfortunately he never fails, he follows the same routine every time.

It was really fun to see both couples and singles alike taking turns with each other on the dance floor. The music was good and went well past midnight. Really fun time if you like salsa.
